pUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHow%20Is%20Giving%20A%20Report%20A%20Crime%3F%26quot%3B%20Supreme%20Court%20In%20Editors%20Guild%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMaking%20some%20striking%20observations%20in%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20said%20that%20the%20crime%20of%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%2C%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Manipur%20Police%20FIR%2C%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20made%20out.%20The%20court%20also%20wondered%20how%20merely%20giving%20a%20report%20could%20constitute%20a%20crime.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20case%20had%20been%20filed%20against%20three%20members%20of%20the%20Editors%20Guild's%20fact-finding%20team%2C%20who%20had%20gone%20to%20Manipur%20to%20assess%20the%20media's%20reportage%20of%20the%20ethnic%20conflict%20in%20the%20state%2C%20and%20the%20Guild's%20president.%20The%20complainant%20had%20alleged%20that%20the%20report%20submitted%20by%20the%20team%20was%20%26quot%3Bfalse%2C%20fabricated%20and%20sponsored%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20the%20charges%20in%20the%20first%20information%20report%20included%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20different%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20hearing%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20and%20justices%20J%20B%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPrima%20facie%2C%20the%20crime%20mentioned%20in%20the%20FIR%20does%20not%20appear%20to%20be%20made%20out.%20There%20is%20no%20whisper%20of%20crime%20in%20the%20complaint%20based%20on%20which%20the%20FIR%20has%20been%20registered.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENoting%20that%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20team%20had%20been%20invited%20to%20Manipur%20by%20the%20Army%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Solicitor%20General%2C%20the%20Army%20writes%20to%20the%20EGI.%20Army%20says%20that%20there%20was%20partisan%20reporting.%20They%20go%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20submit%20a%20report.%20They%20may%20be%20right%20or%20wrong.%20This%20is%20what%20free%20speech%20is%20all%20about.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20asked%20the%20complainant%20why%20the%20FIR%20should%20not%20be%20quashed%20and%20gave%20two%20weeks%20for%20a%20reply.%20Extending%20the%20interim%20relief%20given%20to%20the%20journalists%2C%20the%20court%20said%20no%20action%20can%20be%20taken%20against%20them%20until%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20report%2C%20published%20on%20September%202%2C%20the%20Guild%20had%20said%20there%20were%20clear%20indications%20that%20the%20Manipur%20leadership%20had%20become%20partisan%20during%20the%20conflict.%20It%20was%20also%20critical%20of%20the%20internet%20ban%20in%20the%20state%2C%20which%20it%20said%20was%20detrimental%20to%20reportage%2C%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bone-sided%20reporting%26quot%3B%20by%20some%20media%20outlets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresenting%20the%20complainant%2C%20senior%20advocate%20S%20Guru%20Krishnakumar%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20a%20report%20which%20ferments%20further%20animosity%20between%20groups.%20If%20this%20is%20a%20fact-finding%20report%2C%20as%20they%20claim%2C%20then%20it%20should%20have%20100-200%20photos%20of%20people%20from%20other%20communities%20who%20have%20suffered%20damage.%20The%20reason%20I'm%20referring%20to%20all%20this%20is%20that%20the%20petitioner%20is%20trying%20to%20project%20a%20picture%20that%20a%20completely%20unbiased%20report%20has%20been%20submitted%2C%20but%20it%20is%20far%20from%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAppearing%20for%20the%20Manipur%20government%2C%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%20said%20the%20court%20may%20extend%20the%20interim%20protection%20to%20the%20journalists%20and%20transfer%20the%20plea%20to%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20if%20the%20bench%20wanted%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20September%204%2C%20Manipur%20Chief%20Minister%20N%20Biren%20Singh%20had%20said%20that%20a%20case%20had%20been%20registered%20against%20Editors%20Guild%20president%20Seema%20Mustafa%2