ple%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20are%20retired%20or%20heading%20into%20retirement%20are%20doing%20so%20at%20a%20time%20when%20two%20economic%20forces%20are%20working%20against%20them%3A%20housing%20costs%20and%20an%20end%20to%20pandemic-era%20aid%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Social%20Security%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20average%20Social%20Security%20benefit%20is%20now%20%241%2C706%20per%20month%2C%20more%20than%20%24300%20below%20the%20nearly%20record-high%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frent-prices-all-time-high-us-housing-market-mortgage-rates-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enational%20median%20rent%20price%20of%20%242%2C052%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERent%20increases%20have%20hit%20Florida%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prb.org%2Fresources%2Fwhich-us-states-are-the-oldest%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond-highest%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20citizens%2065%20or%20older%20and%20the%20largest%20total%20number%20of%20people%20that%20age%20and%20above%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20hard.%20Half%20of%20the%2020%20metro%20cities%20with%20the%20steepest%20rent%20increases%20since%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic%20are%20in%20Florida%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Feconomy%2Fhousing%2Fwhy-more-baby-boomers-are-homeless-2d2b913b%3Fstream%3Dbusiness%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20of%20all%20retirees%20who%20moved%20to%20a%20new%20state%20in%202022%2C%2011.8%25%20went%20to%20Florida.%20North%20Carolina%2C%20at%209.6%25%2C%20was%20the%20only%20other%20state%20close%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20as%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fhealthcare%2Fthe-upheaval-at-americas-disappearing-nursing-homes-in-charts-9aa8d2f9%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmericans%2065%20or%20older%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%3C%2Fa%3E%2045%25%20between%202020%20and%202040%2C%20from%2056%20million%20to%2081%20million%2C%20the%20volume%20of%20available%20affordable%20housing%20is%20shrinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20analysis%20of%20federal%20data%20found%20the%20US%20had%20at%20least%20600%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fhealthcare%2Fthe-upheaval-at-americas-disappearing-nursing-homes-in-charts-9aa8d2f9%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efewer%20nursing%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20it%20did%20in%202017.%20In%20Florida%2C%20there%20are%20long%20waiting%20lists%20for%20low-cost%20senior%20housing%20and%20long-term%20care%20facilities%20paid%20for%20by%20Medicaid%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%20A%20Florida%20Housing%20Coalition%20study%20found%20the%20state%20had%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflhousing.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2FHome-Matters-Report-2022.pdfafford%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E25%20affordable%20and%20available%20rental%20units%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20every%20100%20extremely%20low-income%20renters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGovernment%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhomelessness-increasing-united-states-housing-costs-e1990ac7%3Fmod%3Darticle_inline%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobtained%20by%20the%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20homelessness%20was%20up%2011%25%20from%202022%2C%20which%20would%20crush%20the%20previous%20record%20of%202.7%25%20in%202019%2C%20and%20the%20end%20of%20COVID-19%20relief%20is%20not%20helping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20COVID-relief%20funds%20provided%20a%20buffer%2C%26quot%3B%20Donald%20Whitehead%20Jr.%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20at%20the%20National%20Coalition%20for%20the%20Homeless%2C%20told%20the%20Journal.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20what%20happens%20when%20those%20resources%20aren't%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20is%20the%20expansion%20of%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Assistance%20Program%20benefits%20to%20help%20feed%20low-income%20families%20during%20the%20earlier%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillions-americans-hunger-cliff-snap-benefits-food-stamps-getting-cut-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecame%20to%20a%20halt%20in%20March%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20one%20point%20in%202021%2C%20the%20program%20was%20believed%20to%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Fresearch%2Fpublication%2Feffect-reevaluated-thrifty-food-plan-and-emergency-allotments-supplemental%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekept%204.2%20million%20out%20of%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20COVID-19-relief%20resources%2C%20many%20older%20people%20are%20relying%20even%20more%20on%20their%20Social%20Security%20benefits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fpri%2Ftopics%2Fwork-finances-retirement%2Fsocial-security%2Fsocial-security-legislative-activity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20AARP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2045%25%20of%20people%2065%20or%20older%20rely%20on%20Social%20Security%20for%20at%20least%20half%20of%20their%20income%2C%20and%20the%20payments%20keep%2016%20million%20older%20Americans%20out%20of%20poverty%20each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20housing%20continues%20to%20become%20harder%20to%20find%20and%20costs%20continue%20to%20skyrocket%2C%20older%20Americans%20will%20increasingly%20need%20to%20find%20other%20forms%20of%20income%2C%20or%20the%20homelessness%20crisis%20will%20almost%20certainly%20get%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-late-baby-boomers-homeless-rent-social-security-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694772001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65030d78992da60019ec4278%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-late-baby-boomers-homeless-rent-social-security-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20baby%20boomers%20are%20facing%20homelessness%20as%20rent%20prices%20outpace%20Social%20Security%20payments.%20A%20subsidized%20housing%20shortage%20compounds%20the%20problem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cgaines%40insider.com%20(Cork%20Gaines)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-late-baby-boomers-homeless-rent-social-security-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Arm's%20red-hot%20stock%20debut%20captures%20the%20AI%20hype%20but%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20IPO%20market%20has%20rebounded%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225285%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Arm%20IPO%2C%20public%20stock%20trading%20chip%20maker%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6503378c1afe8f0019ea95d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222642%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArm%20soared%20more%20than%2020%25%20in%20its%20public%20trading%20debut%20Thursday.%3Cp%3EMichael%20M.%20Santiago%20%2F%20Getty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EArm%20stock%20soared%2024%25%20on%20its%20first%20day%20of%20trading%20following%20its%20massive%20IPO.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors%20are%20cheering%20the%20debut%2C%20though%20some%20experts%20remain%20hesitant%20to%20use%20Arm%20to%20gauge%20the%20broader%20IPO%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESky-high%20valuations%20and%20easy%20money%20during%20the%20pandemic%20fizzled%20out%20and%20the%20IPO%20market%20has%20been%20in%20a%20slump.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EArm's%20strong%20trading%20debut%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20initial%20public%20offering%20market%20will%20come%20roaring%20back.%20Experts%20say%20it's%20mostly%20a%20sign%20of%20the%20times%20and%20captures%20investors'%20massive%20hype%20around%20tech%20and%20artificial%20intelligence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Farm-ipo-stock-price-chip-designer-trading-nasdaq-tech-stocks-2023-9%3F_gl%3D1*3bn0ci*_ga*MjA5NTAyMzYyOS4xNjYyNDcwMDc5*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5NDcwNzQ2Ny4xMjY2LjEuMTY5NDcxMDQzOC4zMy4wLjA.%5C%22%3EArm%20closed%2024%25%20higher%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20its%20first%20day%20of%20trading%20on%20Thursday%2C%20with%20investors%20pushing%20the%20stock%20to%20%2463.59%20a%20share%2C%20well%20above%20its%20IPO%20price%20of%20%2451.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Softbank-backed%20tech%20company%2C%20which%20designs%20the%20chips%20used%20in%20most%20of%20the%20world's%20smartphones%2C%20raised%20about%20%244.9%20billion%20in%20its%20public%20offering%20and%20secured%20a%20%2454.5%20billion%20valuation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Morgan%2C%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20Synovus%20Trust%20Company%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20stock%20pop%20Thursday%20points%20less%20to%20an%20IPO%20resurgence%20and%20more%20to%20the%20enthusiasm%20around%20artificial%20intelligence.%20It's%20no%20accident%20that%20the%20debut%20came%20relatively%20soon%20after%20Nvidia's%20blowout%20earnings.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hate%20to%20say%20this%2C%20but%20there%20are%20some%20similarities%20between%20this%20AI%20mania%20and%20the%20dot-com%20mania%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Morgan%2C%20a%20three-decade%20market%20veteran.%20%26quot%3BAny%20company%20that%20has%20anything%20to%20do%20with%20AI%20that%20hasn't%20gone%20public%2C%20I'm%20sure%20investment%20bankers%20are%20knocking%20on%20their%20door%20saying%20AI%20is%20hot%2C%20take%20advantage%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20always%20the%20question%2C%20is%20this%20a%20new%20renaissance%20in%20the%20IPO%20space%3F%20But%20I%20think%20the%20Arm%20deal%20is%20kind%20of%20specific%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20said%20the%20IPO%20market%20generally%20will%20likely%20remain%20more%20deal-specific%20around%20the%20red-hot%20technology%20sector.%20Upcoming%20deals%20that%20aren't%20tied%20to%20AI%20or%20tech%2C%20in%20his%20view%2C%20will%20see%20a%20more%20muted%20reception.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Chuckie%20Reddy%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20fintech%20venture%20capital%20firm%20QED%20Investors%2C%20if%20Arm%20shares%20had%20traded%20down%20on%20their%20first%20day%2C%20that%20would%20have%20been%20bad%20news%20for%20the%20IPO%20market.%20But%20their%20big%20first-day%20surge%20doesn't%20necessarily%20open%20the%20floodgates%20for%20more%20public%20offerings.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it%20went%20poorly%2C%20that%20would%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20very%20negative%20signal%2C%20that%20the%20market%20wasn't%20ready%20for%20companies%20to%20go%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20Reddy%20told%20Insider%20on%20Thursday.%20%26quot%3BBut%20since%20it%20went%20smoothly%2C%20it's%20somewhat%20of%20a%20neutral%20signal.%20I%20don't%20think%20it%20materially%20increases%20the%20odds%20that%20others%20will%20go%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20shift%20their%20priorities%20from%20growth%20to%20profitability%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20and%20that%20transition%20hasn't%20fully%20happened%20yet.%20A%20number%20of%20portfolio%20companies%20at%20QED%2C%20he%20said%2C%20are%20planning%20to%20go%20public%20closer%20to%20the%20end%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArm%20marks%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Farm-shares-start-trading-biggest-ipo-almost-two-years%3Futm_medium%3Dingest%26utm_source%3Dmarkets%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20US%20initial%20public%20offering%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202021%2C%20back%20when%20liquidity%20was%20high%20and%20money%20was%20cheap.%20The%20broader%20IPO%20market%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Farm-ipo-instacart-market-dot-com-bubble-investors-finance-stocks-2023-9%5C%22%3Estuck%20in%20a%20pandemic%20hangover%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20raising%20interest%20rates%2C%20and%20both%20investors%20and%20companies%20have%20had%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20lower%20valuations%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20or%20two%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20deal%20on%20investors'%20radar%20will%20be%20Instacart%2C%20which%20was%20worth%20over%20%2430%20billion%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20It%20is%20targeting%20a%20valuation%20in%20its%20upcoming%20IPO%20of%20just%20over%20%249%20billion.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farm-ipo-stock-price-tech-stocks-trading-debut-ai-chips-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694772001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650365e52a72d60019d5568d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Farm-ipo-stock-price-tech-stocks-trading-debut-ai-chips-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Softbank-backed%20chip%20designer%20soared%20more%20than%2020%25%20within%20minutes%20of%20debuting%20on%20public%20markets%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22prosen%40insider.com%20(Phil%20Rosen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Farm-ipo-stock-price-tech-stocks-trading-debut-ai-chips-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22California%20legislature%20passes%20law%20aiming%20to%20protect%20children%20from%20abusers%20during%20custody%20disputes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221186%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Senator%20Susan%20Rubio%20speaks%20at%20a%20podium%20surrounded%20by%20people%20holding%20signs%2C%20including%20one%20that%20reads%20%26quot%3BPass%20Piqui's%20Law.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650375522a72d60019d56e95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22890%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECalifornia%20State%20Senator%20Susan%20Rubio%20advocates%20for%20Piqui's%20Law%20at%20a%20July%2010%20press%20conference.%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20Senate%20Democrats%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPrograms%20that%20treat%20%26quot%3Bparental%20alienation%26quot%3B%20can%20leave%20kids%20with%20alleged%20abusers%20for%20months%20or%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECalifornia's%20legislature%20unanimously%20passed%20Piqui's%20Law%2C%20named%20after%20a%205-year-old%20murdered%20by%20his%20father%20following%20a%20custody%20dispute.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20law%20will%20bar%20judges%20from%20ordering%20children%20into%20many%20parental%20alienation%20treatment%20programs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20was%20reported%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20nonprofit%20newsroom%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.typeinvestigations.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EType%20Investigations%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%20and%20again%2C%20Ana%20Estevez%20warned%20officials%20that%20the%20man%20she%20was%20divorcing%2C%20Aramazd%20Andressian%2C%20was%20abusive%20and%20dangerous.%20Nevertheless%2C%20a%20Los%20Angeles%20County%20family%20court%20judge%20granted%20him%20shared%20custody%20of%20their%205-year-old%20son%2C%20Piqui.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20week%20later%2C%20on%20April%2021%2C%202017%2C%20Andressian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Flocal%2Fcrime%2Fla-me-andressian-sentencing-murder-20170823-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmothered%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20boy%20to%20death.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngulfed%20by%20grief%2C%20Estevez%2C%20a%20former%20elementary-school%20principal%2C%20teamed%20up%20with%20her%20state%20senator%2C%20Susan%20Rubio%2C%20to%20craft%20legislation%20to%20prevent%20other%20children%20from%20being%20ordered%20into%20the%20custody%20of%20their%20abusers.%20This%20week%2C%20the%20California%20legislature%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flegiscan.com%2FCA%2Ftext%2FSB331%2F2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epassed%20that%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BPiqui's%20Law.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20voting%20unanimously%20for%20passage%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20state%20assembly%20gave%20Estevez%20a%20standing%20ovation.%20Estevez%20also%20attended%20Thursday's%20Senate%20vote%2C%20holding%20an%20urn%20containing%20Piqui's%20ashes.%20That%20vote%20was%20unanimous%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20law%2C%20which%20will%20take%20effect%20unless%20it's%20vetoed%20by%20the%20governor%2C%20establishes%20training%20on%20domestic%20and%20child%20abuse%20for%20custody%20judges%20and%20bars%20them%20from%20ordering%20children%20who%20resist%20contact%20with%20one%20of%20their%20parents%20into%20%26quot%3Breunification%20treatment%26quot%3B%20that%20cuts%20them%20off%20from%20the%20other%20parent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20last%20provision%20is%20a%20heavy%20blow%20to%20reunification%20programs%20built%20on%20the%20concept%20of%20%26quot%3Bparental%20alienation.%26quot%3B%20This%20controversial%20theory%2C%20which%20hasn't%20been%20accepted%C2%A0by%20the%20psychiatric%20establishment%2C%20posits%20that%20when%20children%20of%20divorce%20accuse%20a%20parent%20of%20maltreatment%20or%20abuse%2C%20it's%20often%20because%20the%20parent%20they%20prefer%20has%20coached%20them%20to%20lie.%20Some%20programs%20that%20claim%20to%20address%20alienation%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buildingfamilybridges.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFamily%20Bridges%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fturningpointsforfamilies.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETurning%20Points%20for%20Families%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flynnsteinberg.com%2Freunification-therapy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Family%20at%20a%20Time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20ask%20judges%20to%20remove%20children%20from%20the%20home%20of%20the%20preferred%20parent%20and%20prohibit%20that%20parent%20from%20contact%20with%20the%20children%20for%20at%20least%2090%20days.%20In%20practice%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparental-alienation-syndrome-father-alleged-child-abuse-win-custody-case-2023-5%5C%22%3Ean%20investigation%20by%20Insider%20and%20Type%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0found%20that%20the%20separations%20sometimes%20last%20years%20and%20leave%20children%20isolated%20with%20their%20abusers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFamily%20court%20judges%20have%20sent%20hundreds%20of%20children%2C%20many%20of%20them%20from%20California%2C%20to%20such%20programs%2C%20and%20both%20Family%20Bridges%20and%20One%20Family%20at%20a%20Time%20are%20based%20in%20the%20state.%20Piqui's%20Law%20would%20close%20off%20these%20programs'%20pipeline%20of%20referrals%20from%20California%20courts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%20people%20from%20around%20the%20country%20who%20were%20sent%20to%20reunification%20programs%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparental-alienation-syndrome-father-alleged-child-abuse-win-custody-case-2023-5%5C%22%3Etold%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20clinicians%20pressured%20them%20to%20recant%20their%20allegations%20of%20abuse%2C%20sometimes%20threatening%20to%20commit%20them%20to%20psychiatric%20facilities%20or%20separate%20them%20from%20siblings.%20Many%20young%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fadult-children-parental-alienation-treatment-therapy-program-experience-2023-5%5C%22%3Edescribed%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20apart%20from%20the%20parent%20they%20trusted%20as%20acutely%20painful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20family%20court%20and%20beyond%2C%20%26quot%3Beveryone%20is%20more%20comfortable%20believing%20that%20abuse%20didn't%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Danielle%20Pollack%2C%20policy%20manager%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.law.gwu.edu%2Fnational-family-violence-law-center%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Family%20Violence%20Law%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20George%20Washington%20University.%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%2C%20as%20long%20as%20we%20keep%20denying%20abuse%2C%20children%20will%20keep%20getting%20sent%20into%20harm's%20way.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETargeted%20judicial%20training%20could%20help%2C%20Pollack%20said%2C%20since%20abusers%20can%20be%20charming%20and%20persuasive%20in%20the%20courtroom.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20the%20average%20person%20who%20has%20no%20knowledge%20about%20these%20family-abuse%20dynamics%20or%20how%20perpetrators%20operate%2C%20they%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20think%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'I%20can't%20tell%20who's%20lying.'%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D3448062%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Joan%20Meier%2C%20the%20center's%20director%2C%20found%20that%20when%20women%20raised%20allegations%20of%20spousal%20or%20child%20abuse%20during%20custody%20cases%2C%20judges%20believed%20them%20only%2036%25%20of%20the%20time.%20In%20cases%20where%20fathers%20countered%20by%20claiming%20alienation%2C%20judges%20were%20even%20less%20likely%20to%20credit%20mothers%2C%20she%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPollack%20and%20Meier%20helped%20draft%20federal%20legislation%2C%20passed%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Violence%20Against%20Women%20Act%20in%202022%2C%20that%20incentivizes%20states%20to%20implement%20protections%20for%20children%20during%20custody%20disputes.%20To%20qualify%20for%20funding%20under%20Kayden's%20Law%2C%20named%20after%20a%20Pennsylvania%20girl%20who%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.inquirer.com%2Fphilly%2Fnews%2Fcrime%2Fkayden-mancuso-jeff-mancuso-murder-suicide-manayunk-girl-murder-suicide-langhorne-20180807.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emurdered%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20her%20father%20during%20a%20court-ordered%20visit%20in%202018%2C%20a%20state%20must%20require%20extensive%20training%20for%20custody%20judges%20on%20abuse%20and%20trauma%20and%20prohibit%20them%20from%20ordering%20reunification%20treatment%20that%20isolates%20children%20from%20their%20preferred%20parent%2C%20among%20other%20measures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Rubio%20sponsored%20a%20version%20of%20Piqui's%20Law%20but%20withdrew%20the%20bill%20amid%20fierce%20opposition%20from%20judges%20over%20the%20mandatory%20training.%20While%20this%20year's%20version%20establishes%20a%20robust%20curriculum%20for%20judges%20on%20the%20dynamics%20of%20emotional%2C%20physical%2C%20and%20sexual%20abuse%2C%20it%20doesn't%20require%20a%20set%20number%20of%20training%20hours.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20gained%20momentum%20over%20the%20past%20year%20thanks%20to%20heightened%20public%20awareness%20about%20reunification%20programs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20October%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparental-alienation-therapy-siblings-turn-to-instagram-to-speak-out-2023-5%5C%22%3Egraphic%3C%2Fa%3E%20footage%20of%20two%20terrified%20children%20being%20forcibly%20seized%20for%20One%20Family%20at%20a%20Time%20and%20thrust%20into%20an%20SUV%20went%20viral%20on%20TikTok%2C%20sparking%20an%20explosion%20of%20outraged%20comments.%20The%20previous%20day%2C%20the%20elder%20sibling%2C%20Maya%2C%20then%2015%2C%20had%20testified%20in%20family%20court%20that%20her%20mother%20was%20abusive%2C%20but%20her%20mother%20denied%20the%20allegations%20and%20Judge%20Rebecca%20Connolly%20found%20that%20they%20weren't%20credible.%20Connolly%20ordered%20Maya%20and%20her%20brother%2C%20Sebastian%2C%20into%20their%20mother's%20custody%2C%20banned%20their%20father%20and%20all%20his%20relatives%20from%20contacting%20the%20children%2C%20and%20authorized%20an%20intervention%20company%20to%20transport%20them%20to%20a%20four-day%20workshop%20led%20by%20the%20program's%20director%2C%20the%20therapist%20Lynn%20Steinberg.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20May%2C%20Maya%20and%20Sebastian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparental-alienation-therapy-siblings-turn-to-instagram-to-speak-out-2023-5%5C%22%3Eran%20away%20from%20their%20mother's%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20Washington%20state%20and%20made%20their%20way%20back%20to%20Santa%20Cruz%2C%20where%20they%20went%20into%20hiding%20and%20posted%20videos%20about%20their%20ordeal.%20At%20a%20California%20state%20Assembly%20Judiciary%20Committee%20hearing%20on%20July%2011%2C%20Maya%20testified%20in%20support%20of%20Piqui's%20Law%20by%20phone%2C%20saying%20she'd%20been%20treated%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20criminal%26quot%3B%20after%20reporting%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20weeks%20later%2C%20Connolly%20ruled%20that%20Maya%20and%20Sebastian%20could%20return%20home%20to%20their%20father%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20current%20limbo%20the%20minor%20children%20are%20in%20is%20not%20safe.%26quot%3B%20But%20Connolly%20still%20characterized%20the%20children's%20allegations%20against%20their%20mother%20as%20%26quot%3Bfalse.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20July%2011%20hearing%2C%20Estevez%2C%20too%2C%20criticized%20a%20California%20family%20court's%20response%20to%20her%20reports%20of%20abuse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPiqui%20was%20fearful%20of%20his%20father%20and%20repeatedly%20begged%2C%20'Please%20don't%20make%20me%20go%2C%20Mama%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20testified.%20%26quot%3BThe%20horrendous%20decisions%20made%20by%20the%20judges%20who%20presided%20over%20my%20case%20empowered%20my%20ex-husband%20to%20methodically%20plan%20and%20execute%20the%20murder%20of%20my%20only%20child.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2015%20years%2C%20962%20children%20around%20the%20country%20have%20been%20murdered%20by%20a%20parental%20figure%20involved%20in%20a%20separation%2C%20divorce%2C%20or%20other%20family%20court%20dispute%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcenterforjudicialexcellence.org%2F2023%2F07%2F17%2Fcje-releases-child-safety-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20Judicial%20Excellence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20California%20nonprofit%20that%20helped%20draft%20both%20Kayden's%20Law%20and%20the%202022%20version%20of%20Piqui's%20Law.%20The%20center%20has%20classified%20135%20of%20these%20murders%20as%20%26quot%3Bpreventable%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20because%2C%20as%20in%20Piqui's%20case%2C%20one%20parent%20had%20presented%20evidence%20to%20the%20court%20that%20the%20other%20parent%20wasn't%20safe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20with%20the%20most%20preventable%20child%20homicides%20is%20California%2C%20with%2025%2C%20according%20to%20the%20center.%20Florida%20is%20second%2C%20with%2010.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20law%20takes%20effect%2C%20California%20judges%20will%20be%20prohibited%20from%20ordering%20reunification%20treatment%20that%20entails%20a%20custody%20transfer%2C%20a%20no-contact%20order%2C%20forcible%20transport%2C%20overnight%20travel%2C%20threats%2C%20or%20other%20%26quot%3Bacutely%20distressing%20circumstances.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20girl%20speaks%20before%20the%20California%20State%20Senate%20with%20her%20mother%20at%20her%20side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65037773956dba001acdde5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJill%20Montes%20stands%20by%20as%20her%20daughter%20testifies%20before%20the%20California%20State%20Senate%20on%20April%2025.%20The%20girl%20said%20that%20since%20being%20sent%20to%20a%20parental%20alienation%20treatment%20program%2C%20she's%20experienced%20anxiety%20and%20depression.%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20State%20Senate%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EAt%20a%20hearing%20in%20Sacramento%20in%20April%2C%20the%20state's%20Senate%20Judiciary%20Committee%20heard%20testimony%20from%20a%2010-year-old%20girl%20from%20Carlsbad%20who%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fparental-alienation-syndrome-father-alleged-child-abuse-win-custody-case-2023-5%5C%22%3Eremoved%20from%20her%20mother%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jill%20Montes%2C%20in%202022%20and%20sent%20to%20Family%20Bridges%20with%20her%20father%2C%20Thomas%20Winenger%2C%20and%20two%20of%20her%20siblings.%20That%20was%20despite%20a%20finding%20by%20Child%20Welfare%20Services%20that%20Winenger%20had%20abused%20her%20brother.%20The%20girl%20testified%20that%20since%20the%20program%2C%20she%20and%20her%20siblings%20have%20struggled%20with%20post-traumatic%20stress%20disorder%2C%20anxiety%2C%20and%20depression.%3Cp%3EWinenger%20was%20eventually%20arrested%20on%20child%20pornography%20and%20sexual-abuse%20charges.%20He%20has%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20and%20is%20awaiting%20trial.%20Montes%20officially%20regained%20custody%20in%20late%20May.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpponents%20of%20Piqui's%20Law%20have%20included%20not%20only%20judges%20but%20parents%20who%20said%20they%20were%20victims%20of%20parental%20alienation%20and%20therapists%20who%20claim%20to%20treat%20it%2C%20including%20Steinberg.%20She%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20without%20treatment%2C%20children%20who've%20been%20alienated%20from%20a%20parent%20may%20suffer%20long-term%20guilt%20and%20shame%2C%20along%20with%20eating%20disorders%2C%20drug%20addiction%2C%20depression%2C%20gender%20dysphoria%2C%20and%20other%20conditions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOfficials%20from%20Family%20Bridges%20and%20Turning%20Points%20have%20repeatedly%20turned%20down%20requests%20for%20interviews.%20Recently%2C%20the%20Turning%20Points%20director%2C%20Linda%20Gottlieb%2C%20said%20she%20would%20only%20consider%20allowing%20Insider%20to%20interview%20her%20if%20she%20could%20interview%20Insider%20first.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20Psychiatric%20Association%20and%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20have%20both%20rejected%20proposals%20to%20recognize%20alienation%20as%20a%20psychiatric%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20legislatures%20in%20Maryland%2C%20Tennessee%2C%20and%20Colorado%20have%20also%20passed%20some%20of%20the%20protections%20recommended%20by%20Kayden's%20Law.%20The%20Justice%20Department%20will%20determine%20which%20states%2C%20if%20any%2C%20qualify%20for%20the%20federal%20funding%2C%20Pollack%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-parental-alienation-law-family-court-child-abuse-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694772001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650375522a72d60019d56e95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-parental-alienation-law-family-court-child-abuse-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Piqui's%20Law%20will%20bar%20family%20court%20judges%20from%20ordering%20children%20into%20many%20'parental%20alienation'%20treatment%20programs%2C%20which%20have%20sometimes%20left%20children%20in%20the%20custody%20of%20their%20abusers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22oliviagentile%40mac.com%20(Olivia%20Gentile)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-parental-alienation-law-family-court-child-abuse-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Luis%20Rubiales%20in%20Spanish%20court%20over%20Women's%20W