y.%20Almost%20all%20of%20his%20wealth%20comes%20from%20Meta%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20data-pm-slice%3D%5C%221%201%20%5B%5D%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%20was%20once%20the%20world's%20third-richest%20person.%20He's%20now%20fallen%20to%2010th%20place%2C%20but%20he's%20still%20worth%20%24108%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20estimates%20by%20the%20Bloomberg%20Billionaires%20Index.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20is%20the%20co-founder%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-owns-facebook%5C%22%3ECEO%20of%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-apps%5C%22%3EFacebook%20and%20sister%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20Instagram%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20now%20Threads%20among%20its%20products%20alongside%20Reality%20Labs%2C%20the%20division%20that%20houses%20its%20metaverse%20and%20VR%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20Zuckerberg%20become%20a%20billionaire%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20was%20a%20computer%20nerd%20from%20a%20young%20age.%20While%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20he%20started%20social%20network%20%26quot%3BThe%20Facebook%26quot%3B%20with%20some%20friends%20in%202004%20as%20a%20way%20to%20connect%20students.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngel%20investor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-peter-thiel-strange-relationship-contrarian-max-chafkin-2021-9%5C%22%3EPeter%20Thiel%3C%2Fa%3E%20gave%20him%20%24500%2C000%20in%20funding%20in%202004.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20Facebook%20had%20nearly%201%20million%20users.%20Zuckerberg%20dropped%20out%20of%20Harvard%20in%202005%20to%20work%20on%20it%20full-time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202005%2C%20Accel%20Partners%20invested%20%2412.7%20million%20in%20Facebook%2C%20reportedly%20valuing%20the%20company%20at%20%2487.5%20million.%20The%20next%20year%2C%20Zuckerberg%20turned%20down%20an%20offer%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-