man%20and%20with%20music%20from%20Taylor%20Swift.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-wales-66795868%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-wales-66795868.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-wales-66795868.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Profile%20in%20Courage%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15103802%2F8R4A9966.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20a%20copy%20of%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%E2%80%99s%20latest%20book%20%3Cem%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20the%20following%20inscription%3A%20%E2%80%9CTo%20Khurshid%2C%20in%20remembrance%20of%20six%20decades%20of%20friendship.%E2%80%9D%20Our%20friendship%20actually%20goes%20back%20six%20decades%20plus%20two%20years.%20In%20fact%20in%202011%2C%20which%20was%2050th%20anniversary%20of%20Class%20of%201961%20(Trinity%20Hall%2C%20Cambridge)%2C%20we%20were%20both%20honoured%20by%20our%20college%20to%20speak%20at%20the%20%E2%80%98Class%20Reunion%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20Pak-India%20peace%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%E2%80%99s%20memoir%20covers%20the%20first%2050%20years%20of%20his%20life%2C%20but%20I%20have%20no%20doubt%20that%20he%20will%20eventually%20write%20about%20the%20next%20three%20decades%20of%20his%20very%20eventful%20life%20too%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20time%20when%20we%20were%20both%20cabinet%20ministers%20in%20our%20respective%20countries%20and%20worked%20together%20to%20improve%20relations%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20impression%20on%20meeting%20him%20was%20that%20the%20volume%20of%20his%20voice%20was%20quite%20disproportionate%20to%20the%20size%20of%20his%20body.%20Only%20later%20did%20I%20realise%20that%20the%20resonance%20in%20his%20voice%20was%20also%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20clarity%20of%20his%20thoughts%20and%20strength%20of%20his%20conscience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20writes%20in%20his%20book%20under%20%E2%80%98Cambridge%20at%20First%20Sight%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20gong%20sounded%20and%20we%20filed%20into%20%E2%80%98hall%E2%80%99%20together%20(Cambridge%20jargon%20for%20%E2%80%98dinner%E2%80%99).%20As%20I%20worked%20my%20way%20through%20a%20tasteless%20piece%20of%20unspiced%20meat%20and%20boiled%20vegetables%2C%20little%20did%20I%20know%20that%20my%20first%20meal%20in%20Cambridge%20was%20in%20the%20distinguished%20company%20of%20the%20man%20who%20was%20to%20become%20the%20best%20foreign%20minister%20Pakistan%20has%20ever%20had!%E2%80%9D%20This%20remark%20could%20get%20me%20into%20trouble%20with%20some%20extremist%20elements%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20and%20I%20have%20been%20friends%20ever%20since%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20there%20was%20an%20unstated%20%E2%80%98competition%E2%80%99%20between%20us%20as%20to%20who%20would%20make%20it%20to%20becoming%20foreign%20minister%20first.%20It%20so%20happened%20that%20when%20I%20was%20foreign%20minister%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20Mani%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20petroleum%20minister.%20I%20have%20always%20had%20a%20feeling%20that%20he%20should%20have%20made%20it%20to%20the%20foreign%20ministership%20of%20his%20country%20given%20his%20insight%2C%20deep%20understanding%20of%20international%20relations%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20travelled%20from%20the%20foreign%20service%20to%20electoral%20politics%20(not%20a%20common%20phenomenon).%20With%20his%20empathy%20and%20deep%20understanding%20of%20Pakistan-India%20relations%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%20he%20would%20have%20been%20India%E2%80%99s%20finest%20foreign%20minister.%20Mani%2C%20however%2C%20is%20far%20too%20bright%20and%20outspoken%20for%20his%20own%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20bond%20was%20created%20when%20I%20said%20I%20was%20born%20in%20Lahore%2C%20Khurshid%E2%80%99s%20hometown.%20Many%2C%20many%20years%20later%20%E2%80%93%20fifty%20at%20least%20%E2%80%93%20Khurshid%20was%20to%20confide%20in%20me%20that%20the%20reason%20he%20had%20walked%20up%20to%20greet%20me%20was%20that%20he%20had%20never%20before%20met%20a%20Hindu!%20He%20had%20picked%2C%20I%20told%20him%20sourly%2C%20a%20rather%20poor%20example.%E2%80%9D%20I%20need%20to%20clarify%20this%20statement.%20My%20father%20was%20a%20top%20lawyer%20and%20politician%20and%20had%20many%20Hindu%20clients%20and%20political%20colleagues.%20What%20I%20meant%20to%20say%20or%20should%20have%20said%20was%20that%20he%20was%20the%20first%20Hindu%20of%20my%20own%20age%20that%20I%20had%20come%20across%20and%20with%20whom%20I%20can%20interact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20314px)%2085vw%2C%20314px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15103449%2F81X6ggaKJEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22314%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15103449%2F81X6ggaKJEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20663w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15103449%2F81X6ggaKJEL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-199x300.jpg%20199w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-673135%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22474%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EJuggernaut%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMani%E2%80%99s%20frankness%2C%20honesty%20and%20courage%2C%20of%20which%20I%20have%20been%20a%20witness%20all%20my%20life%2C%20comes%20across%20very%20early%20in%20his%20memoirs%3A%20%E2%80%9CMy%20parents%E2%80%99%20wedding%20was%20both%20unusual%20and%20a%20disaster.%20It%20was%20unusual%20because%20it%20was%20held%20in%20the%20bridegroom%E2%80%99s%20house%2C%20not%20the%20bride%E2%80%99s%2C%20for%20my%20poor%20mother%20had%20neither%20home%20nor%20family%20to%20%E2%80%98give%20her%20away%E2%80%99.%20It%20was%20a%20disaster%2C%20because%20they%20had%20hardly%20entered%20the%20nuptial%20chamber%20when%20my%20father%20announced%20that%20he%20had%20really%20wanted%20to%20marry%20my%20mother%E2%80%99s%20sister.%20It%20was%20a%20blow%20from%20which%20the%20marriage%20never%20recovered.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20has%20courted%20controversy%20throughout%20his%20life.%20This%20seems%20to%20have%20got%20him%20into%20trouble%20even%20before%20he%20joined%20the%20foreign%20service%20as%20questions%20were%20raised%20about%20his%20alleged%20membership%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20in%20Britain.%20To%20this%20%E2%80%98allegation%E2%80%99%20he%20responded%20to%20none%20other%20than%20President%20Sarvepalli%20Radhakrishnan%20that%20he%20was%20not%20and%20could%20not%20have%20been%20a%20member%2C%20since%20he%20was%20not%20a%20British%20citizen.%20He%20traces%20the%20ups%20and%20downs%20of%20this%20episode%2C%20his%20hopes%20being%20alternatively%20raised%20and%20then%20dashed%20to%20the%20ground.%20His%20mother%E2%80%99s%20connections%20seem%20to%20have%20stood%20him%20in%20good%20stead%20and%20Mani%20concludes%20the%20entire%20episode%20by%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CNehru%20entirely%20endorsed%20this%2C%20adding%20he%20too%20had%20heard%20good%20reports%20of%20me.%20Thus%2C%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20personal%20signature%2C%20I%20crossed%20my%20personal%20Rubicon%20on%2024%20October%201963.%20It%20had%20been%20worth%20the%20trauma%20I%20had%20undergone%20to%20become%20the%20first%20IFS%20officer%20%E2%80%93%20since%20the%20initial%20formation%20of%20the%20IFS%20back%20in%201946-47%20to%20be%20admitted%20to%20the%20service%20under%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20own%20hands.%E2%80%9D%20(Mani%20was%20lucky%20that%20Nehru%20himself%20was%20a%20Fabian%20socialist).%20One%20of%20his%20friends%20commented%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthey%20found%20you%20to%20be%20a%20Marxist%20%E2%80%93%20but%20of%20a%20Groucho%20variety%E2%80%9D.%20Mani%20further%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIndia%20under%20Nehru%20was%20truly%20a%20democracy.%20Alas!%20Democracy%20is%20disappearing%20even%20when%20I%20write%20these%20words.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20been%20struck%20by%20the%20pace%20of%20efforts%20in%20India%20to%20delegitimise%20Nehru.%20In%20Pakistan%2C%20democracy%20has%20always%20been%20a%20fragile%20plant%20and%20our%20leadership%20too%20has%20committed%20huge%20blunders%20since%20independence%20for%20which%20we%20are%20currently%20paying%20the%20price%20%E2%80%93%20but%20there%20is%20still%20hope%20here%2C%20since%20fortunately%2C%20no%20one%2C%20not%20even%20the%20religious%20parties%2C%20has%20dared%20to%20question%20Muhammad%20Ali%C2%A0Jinnah%E2%80%99s%20legacy%20as%20the%20father%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20independence.%20He%20is%20universally%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%98Quaid-e-Azam%E2%80%99%20and%20his%20personality%20is%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20all%20Pakistanis%20who%20believe%20in%20an%20inclusive%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20is%20exceptionally%20courageous%20for%20a%20politician.%20Politicians%20throughout%20the%20world%20are%20notoriously%20self-serving%20and%20hardly%20ever%20stick%20their%20neck%20out%20to%20say%20something%20that%20would%20displease%20the%20dominant%20leader.%20This%20is%20more%20so%20in%20South%20Asia.%20When%20I%20was%20foreign%20minister%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20improve%20relations%20between%20our%20two%20countries%20through%20various%20means.%20I%20was%20particularly%20keen%20on%20oil%20and%20gas%20connectivity%20and%20would%20often%20refer%20to%20the%20Iran-Pakistan-India%20gas%20pipeline%20and%20TAPI%20(Turkmenistan-Afghanistan-Pakistan-India)%20as%20pipelines%20of%20peace.%20Providentially%2C%20Mani%20was%20petroleum%20minister%20at%20that%20time%2C%20and%20I%20would%20often%20talk%20to%20him%20about%20this.%20In%20my%20more%20idealistic%20moments%2C%20I%20would%20even%20talk%20of%20an%20Iranian%20gas%20pipeline%20passing%20through%20Pakistan%2C%20north%20towards%20China%20and%20south%20towards%20India%2C%20which%20I%20thought%20would%20be%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20the%20realisation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98Asian%20Century%E2%80%99.%20Mani%20was%20equally%20convinced.%20The%20Americans%20were%2C%20however%2C%20unhappy%20and%20Manmohan%20Singh%20suddenly%20referred%20to%20the%20IPP%20as%20an%20un-bankable%20project.%20As%20Mani%E2%80%99s%20views%20were%20at%20variance%20with%20those%20of%20his%20own%20prime%20minister%2C%20Mani%20soon%20lost%20his%20job%20%E2%80%93%20but%20was%20retained%20in%20the%20cabinet%2C%20Manmohan%20Singh%20being%20the%20gentlest%20of%20the%20gentlemen%20I%20have%20met.%20Mani%20continued%20as%20the%20minister%20of%20panchayati%20raj%20and%20other%20portfolios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20respect%2C%20Mani%20and%20I%20share%20similar%20problems.%20Although%20he%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20much%20more%20rash%20than%20I%20am%2C%20he%20has%20not%20had%20to%20undergo%20imprisonment%20as%20I%20have%20during%20both%20Zulfikar%20Ali%20Bhutto%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20and%20General%20Zia%20ul-Haq%E2%80%99s.%20Under%20Zia%2C%20I%20was%20put%20in%20a%20condemned%20prisoner%E2%80%99s%20cell%20for%20six%20month%20and%20during%20the%20heyday%20of%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20I%20had%20to%20resign%20from%20the%20National%20Assembly%20due%20to%20my%20opposition%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98Shariat%20Bill%E2%80%99%20(to%20cut%20a%20long%20story%20short%2C%20my%20resignation%20was%20torn%20to%20bits%20in%20a%20stormy%20parliamentary%20party%20meeting).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Mani%20has%20understood%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%2C%20this%20is%20because%20he%20is%20not%20only%20a%20former%20officer%20of%20the%20foreign%20service%20but%20also%20a%20prolific%20reader%20and%20writer%2C%20which%20gives%20him%20deep%20insight%20into%20the%20Pakistani%20psyche.%20He%20has%20mentioned%20many%20times%20how%20Pakistan-India%20relations%20have%20improved%20under%20President%20Ayub%20Khan%2C%20Zia-ul-Haq%20and%20Musharraf.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20during%20the%20course%20of%20discussions%20on%20Kashmir%20spanning%20over%20approximately%20five%20years%2C%20the%20inputs%20from%20the%20army%20leadership%20were%20neither%20rhetorical%20nor%20laced%20with%20ideological%20spin%20often%20associated%20with%20mid-level%20and%20even%20fairly%20senior%20army%20officers%2C%20but%20invariably%20supported%20by%20reason%20and%20informed%20perspectives.%20However%2C%20some%20clarification%20is%20in%20order.%20First%2C%20irrespective%20of%20its%20form%2C%20the%20role%20of%20the%20government%20as%20an%20institution%20is%20critical%20in%20high-level%20decisions%20involving%20both%20civilian%20and%20military%20elements.%20Since%20from%20the%20outset%2C%20our%20government%20was%20seeking%20a%20solution%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20dispute%20on%20reasonable%20and%20fair%20grounds%2C%20subsequent%20engagement%20focused%20on%20the%20objective%20rather%20than%20attempting%20to%20derail%20the%20process.%20This%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20the%20politicians%20do%20not%20wish%20to%20promote%20good%20relations.%20In%20fact%2C%20every%20major%20political%20leader%2C%20while%20in%20office%2C%20advocated%20good%20relations%20with%20India%20and%20in%20my%20book%2C%20I%20have%20traced%20the%20statements%20of%20these%20leaders%20right%20from%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%20to%20Feroze%20Khan%20Noon%2C%20Z.A.%20Bhutto%2C%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20and%20Imran%20Khan.%20Many%20of%20Mani%E2%80%99s%20speeches%20also%20recognise%20this%20fact.%20I%20am%20sure%20when%20he%20records%20his%20experiences%20from%201991%20to%20date%2C%20he%20will%20be%20able%20to%20say%20this%20with%20great%20clarity%20as%20he%20has%20already%20done%20in%20his%20speeches%20many%20times%20and%20his%20review%20of%20my%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Watch%3A%20'Pakistan%20Is%20My%20Second%20Favourite%20Country%2C'%20Says%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmani-shankar-aiyar-karan-thapar-pakistan%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Pakistan%20Is%20My%20Second%20Favourite%20Country%2C%E2%80%99%20Says%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mischievous%20smile%20%E2%80%93%20depicted%20very%20accurately%20on%20the%20cover%20of%20%3Cem%3EMemoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20is%20representative%20of%20the%20humour%2C%20wit%20and%20one-liners%20which%20sometimes%20get%20him%20into%20trouble.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20narrated%20to%20me%20a%20story%20about%20Natwar%20Singh%2C%20my%20former%20counterpart%20from%20India.%20I%20have%20always%20greatly%20enjoyed%20Natwar%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20company%2C%20and%20he%20and%20I%20were%20able%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20together%20in%20order%20to%20improve%20relations%20between%20our%20countries.%20He%20is%20a%20gracious%20host%20and%20a%20great%20%E2%80%98raconteur%E2%80%99.%20To%20Natwar%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20misfortune%2C%20however%2C%20they%20both%20went%20to%20the%20same%20college%20(though%20perhaps%20a%20decade%20apart).%20According%20to%20Mani%2C%20Natwar%20Singh%20preceded%20him%20and%20wrote%20in%20the%20St.%20Stephens%20College%20guest%20register%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20what%20I%20am%20today%20because%20of%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%E2%80%9D%20to%20which%20Mani%20riposted%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20blame%20the%20college%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20sometimes%20seems%20to%20have%20strange%20sense%20of%20humour.%20I%20had%20the%20misfortune%20of%20asking%20for%20his%20advice%20on%20whether%20I%20should%20visit%20Bombay%20on%20the%20invitation%20of%20Sudhendra%20Kulkarni%20for%20the%20launch%20of%20my%20book%20%3Cem%3ENeither%20a%20Hawk%2C%20nor%20a%20Dove%3C%2Fem%3E%20after%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20had%20threatened%20us%20with%20dire%20consequences%20if%20I%20dared%20to%20land%20in%20Bombay.%20I%20asked%20Mani%20what%20I%20should%20do.%20He%20said%20that%20I%20ought%20to%20go.%20I%20concluded%20that%20as%20my%20friend%2C%20Mani%20anticipated%20no%20danger%20to%20my%20person.%20He%2C%20however%2C%20told%20me%20that%20the%20Shiv%20Sena%20had%20threatened%20him%20similarly%20and%20he%20had%20to%20be%20protected%20by%20a%20huge%20police%20posse.%20I%20was%20not%20sure%20if%20he%20was%20serious%2C%20and%20asked%20him%20whether%20he%20was%20encouraging%20me%20to%20go%20or%20dissuading%20me.%20Nevertheless%2C%20my%20visit%20to%20Bombay%20was%20quite%20adventurous%20and%20helped%20promote%20my%20book%20sales.%20Perhaps%20Mani%20was%20right%20after%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98This%20is%20an%20enemy%20country%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20quotes%20his%20wife%20asking%20him%20while%20returning%20from%20one%20of%20the%20many%20scores%20or%20hundreds%20of%20parties%20that%20he%20may%20have%20attended%20as%20Consul%20General%20in%20Karachi%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20an%20enemy%20country%2C%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%20He%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20a%20question%20that%20haunted%20me%20through%20my%20three%20years%20in%20Karachi%20and%20continues%20to%20haunt%20me.%20Is%20Pakistan%20an%20%E2%80%98enemy%E2%80%99%20country%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mani%2C%20%E2%80%9COne%20of%20the%20most%20important%20lessons%20I%20learnt%20in%20Pakistan%20was%20that%20Indian%20hostility%2C%20or%20even%20the%20apprehension%20of%20such%20hostility%2C%20is%20what%20unites%20Pakistanis%20behind%20their%20government%2C%20military%20or%20civilian%E2%80%A6.%20Across%20a%20wide%20spectrum%20of%20Karachi%20opinion%2C%20I%20found%20a%20clear%20willingness%2C%20indeed%20an%20ardent%20desire%2C%20to%20see%20differences%20with%20India%20settled.%C2%A0I%20searched%20for%20tell-tale%20signs%20from%20business%20barons%20to%20barbers%20and%20bootblacks%3B%20from%20society%20ladies%20in%20expensive%20chiffons%20and%20%E2%80%98suited-booted%E2%80%99%20boxwallahs%20to%20butlers%20and%20domestic%20servants%3B%20from%20politicians%20who%20had%20held%20high%20office%20to%20purveyors%20of%20news%20and%20comment%3B%20from%20intellectuals%20to%20poets%20and%20writers%3B%20from%20artists%20of%20different%20genres%3B%20from%20street%20vendors%20to%20shopkeepers%3B%20from%20English-speaking%20pukka%20sahibs%20to%20die-hard%20Islamic%20nationalists%3B%20from%20the%20religious%20minorities%2C%20ranging%20through%20rich%20ones%20like%20the%20Parsis%20and%20Hindu%20millionaires%2C%20as%20well%20as%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20poor%20Hindu%20haaris%20(sharecroppers)%20of%20Sindhi%20wadehras%20to%20a%20number%20of%20teachers%20in%20Karachi%E2%80%99s%20reputed%20private%20schools%20and%20government%20schools%3B%20and%20from%20the%20sophisticates%20of%20Karachi%20to%20those%20who%20thronged%20the%20Indian%20visa%20area.%C2%A0All%20of%20them%20wanted%20peace%3B%20none%20was%20a%20warmonger%2C%20not%20even%20the%20%E2%80%98Islam-pasand%E2%80%99.%20Bhutto%E2%80%99s%201965%20call%20for%20%E2%80%98a%20thousand%20years%E2%80%99%20war%E2%80%99%20with%20India%20had%20no%20takers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20cannot%20improve%20on%20this%20since%20I%20share%20his%20views%20but%20would%20be%20remiss%20if%20I%20did%20not%20add%20a%20word%20of%20caution.%20There%20is%20both%20good%20and%20bad%20in%20the%20history%20of%20our%20countries%2C%20which%20could%20be%20exploited%20by%20demagogues%20or%20statesmen%20depending%20on%20their%20agendas.%20After%20all%2C%20on%20ten%20occasions%20we%20have%20faced%20war%20or%20near-war%20situations%2C%20the%20last%20war%20being%20in%20Kargil%201999%20and%20a%20near-war%20situation%20being%20the%20Balakot%20airstrike%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20speaks%20very%20fondly%20of%20his%20relationship%20with%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20as%20prime%20minister.%20Speaking%20of%20his%20first%20interaction%20with%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20he%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6I%20briefly%20summarized%20my%20experience%20of%20Pakistani%20public%20opinion%20and%20said%20I%20thought%20an%20emotional%20breakthrough%20was%20the%20prime%20necessity%2C%20what%20I%20called%20a%20%E2%80%98goodwill%C2%A0blitzkrieg%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%2C%20I%20said%2C%20held%20no%20formal%20office%20other%20than%20being%20a%20backbench%20MP%20but%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20whole%20world%20knew%20that%20he%20was%20the%20Indian%20PM%E2%80%99s%20son.%20Hence%2C%20if%20he%20visited%20Pakistan%2C%20nothing%20he%20said%20would%20be%20binding%20on%20the%20Government%20of%20India%3B%20yet%2C%20as%20it%20was%20the%20%3Cem%3Eatmospherics%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20set%20right%2C%20I%20gave%20him%20the%20example%20of%20Crown%20Prince%20Edward%E2%80%99s%20highly%20successful%20personal%20visit%20to%20France%20that%20led%20to%20the%20Anglo-French%20entente%20cordiale%20of%201904%E2%80%A6%20I%20assured%20him%2C%20(he)%20would%20draw%20huge%20crowds%20and%20he%20would%20be%20received%20with%20wild%20enthusiasm.%20This%20rapturous%20welcome%20would%20be%20beamed%20into%20every%20drawing%20room%20in%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20and%20would%20open%20the%20way%2C%20through%20negotiations%2C%20to%20a%20possible%20entente%20cordiale%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan.%20He%20seemed%20interested%20but%20non-committal.%E2%80%9D%20The%20visit%20did%20not%20take%20place%2C%20but%20Mani%20was%20right%20because%20the%20Indian%20and%20Pakistani%20psyche%20likes%20grand%20gestures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Bad%20Advice%20Led%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20To%20Make%20Mistakes%20in%20Handling%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20Issue%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbad-advice-rajiv-gandhi-mistakes-babri-masjid%5C%22%3EHow%20Bad%20Advice%20Led%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20To%20Make%20Mistakes%20in%20Handling%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20Issue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98goodwill%20blitzkrieg%E2%80%99%20that%20Mani%20talks%20about%20was%20achieved%20during%20Musharraf%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20Delhi%20in%202001.%20There%20was%2024%2F7%20coverage%20of%20President%20Musharraf%E2%80%99s%20visit.%20All%20and%20sundry%20pointed%20out%20he%20was%20a%20son%20of%20Delhi%20who%20was%20coming%20back.%20They%20discussed%20and%20described%20in%20great%20detail%20the%20history%20of%20his%20ancestral%20home%20in%20Delhi%2C%20%E2%80%98Neharwali%20Haveli%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20even%20tracked%20down%20his%20old%20nanny%2C%20who%20had%20fond%20memories%20of%20taking%20care%20of%20him%20as%20a%20baby.%20It%20was%20surprising%20to%20see%20how%20the%20man%20who%20was%20accused%20by%20the%20Indian%20media%20of%20being%20the%20main%20person%20behind%20Kargil%20managed%20to%20attract%20such%20positive%20media%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mani%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20never%20really%20understood%20why%20Indian%20diplomacy%20has%20only%20rarely%20and%20fitfully%20considered%20mining%20this%20treasure%20trove%20of%20goodwill%20to%20promote%20good%20relations.%20While%20we%20are%20sure-footed%20in%20Paraguay%2C%20we%20stumble%20in%20neighbouring%20Pakistan!%20%E2%80%A6The%20common%20or%20garden%20Pakistani%20not%20only%20speaks%20the%20same%20language%20as%20us%2C%20and%20shares%20much%20of%20the%20same%20%3Cem%3Etehzeeb%3C%2Fem%3E%20(culture)%2C%20they%20love%20Bollywood%20and%20its%20music%20and%20laugh%20at%20the%20same%20jokes%20and%20befriend%20us%20everywhere%20outside%20the%20subcontinent.%20Almost%20everyone%20who%20has%20served%20in%20Pakistan%20acknowledges%20their%20personal%20goodwill%20towards%20Indians.%E2%80%9D%20Indeed%2C%20there%20are%20similarities%20between%20the%20cultures%20of%20our%20two%20countries%20as%20I%20write%20in%20%3Cem%3ENeither%20a%20Hawk%2C%20Nor%20a%20Dove%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20culturally%20dissimilar%20people%20of%20the%20subcontinent%20are%20united%20by%20the%20shared%20experiences%20of%20being%20burned%20by%20the%20summer%20sun%2C%20the%20sheer%20joy%20of%20monsoon%20rains%20breaking%20the%20summer%20heat%2C%20and%20memories%20of%20various%20foreign%20invasions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeace%20process%20should%20be%20%E2%80%98uninterrupted%20and%20uninterruptible%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20advocates%20a%20peace%20process%20that%20must%20proceed%20uninterrupted%20because%20any%20interruption%20converts%20the%20India-Pakistan%20dialogue%20into%20a%20game%20of%20snakes%20and%20ladders%3A%20the%20mouth%20of%20the%20snake%20swallowing%20up%20all%20the%20climbing%20of%20ladders%2C%20requiring%20the%20negotiators%20to%20start%20again%20from%20square%20one.%20That%20is%20why%2C%20he%20says%2C%20he%20has%20been%20advocating%20the%20need%20for%20a%20restructuring%20of%20the%20dialogue%20to%20make%20it%20%E2%80%98uninterrupted%20and%20uninterruptible%E2%80%99.%20I%20have%20of%20course%20advocated%20the%20same%20for%20years%20and%20would%20like%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20nature%20of%20Pakistan-India%20relations%20is%20such%20that%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20positive%20stimuli%2C%20they%20do%20not%20remain%20on%20an%20even%20keel.%20If%20there%20is%20no%20dialogue%2C%20a%20near%20certainty%20prevails%20that%20relations%20will%20move%20on%20a%20downward%20trajectory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMani%20writes%2C%20%E2%80%9CConflict%2C%20and%20the%20management%20of%20conflict%2C%20is%20the%20realpolitik%20focus.%20And%20that%20is%20why%20people-to-people%20contacts%2C%20in%20regard%20to%20visas%2C%20films%2C%20media%2C%20trade%2C%20tourism%20or%20cultural%20exchanges%20or%20even%20pilgrimages%2C%20are%20the%20first%20to%20be%20sacrificed%20whenever%20governments%20want%20to%20bare%20their%20fangs.%20Sustaining%20distrust%20between%20governments%20is%20easier%20than%20the%20patient%20building%20of%20trust%20between%20people.%E2%80%9D%20Of%20course%2C%20Mani%20is%20right.%20During%20my%20tenure%20as%20foreign%20minister%2C%20I%20felt%20that%20Pakistan-India%20relationship%20could%20be%20made%20more%20predictable%20and%20less%20crisis-prone%20by%20complementing%20governmental%20efforts%20with%20much%20greater%20people-to-people%20interaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20countries%20face%20many%20common%20challenges%2C%20not%20the%20least%20of%20which%20is%20climate%20change%20which%20has%20caused%20havoc%20in%20large%20parts%20of%20the%20subcontinent%20and%20these%20can%20only%20be%20effectively%20addressed%20by%20both%20collectively.%20This%20is%20why%20Mani%20is%20right%20when%20he%20refers%20to%20the%20need%20for%20an%20%E2%80%98uninterrupted%20and%20uninterruptible%E2%80%99%20dialogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKhurshid%20Mahmud%20Kasuri%20served%20as%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20Minister%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%20between%20November%202002%20and%20November%202007.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694756433000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15103802%2F8R4A9966.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fmani-shankar-aiyar-memoirs%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20friend%20and%20colleague%20from%20across%20the%20border%20reflects%20on%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%E2%80%99s%20personality%2C%20career%20and%20methods.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fmani-shankar-aiyar-memoirs%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Finance%20Ministry%20notifies%2031%20state%20benches%20of%20GST%20appellate%20tribunal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694756183000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-06%2F15%2Ffull%2F1623766315-375.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Ffinance-ministry-notifies-31-state-benches-of-gst-appellate-tribunal-123091500240_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20per%20the%20notification%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20UTs%20--%20Dadra%20and%20Nagar%20Haveli%20and%20Daman%20and%20Diu%2C%20will%20have%20two%20benches%20of%20the%20GSTAT%3B%20Goa%20and%20Maharashtra%20together%20will%20have%20three%20benches%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Ffinance-ministr