iness-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-06%2F29%2Ffull%2F1624987926-3201.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fwpi-remains-in-deflation-for-5th-straight-month-at-0-52-in-august-123091401051_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20wholesale%20inflation%20rate%20was%2012.48%20per%20cent%20in%20August%20last%20year%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fwpi-remains-in-deflation-for-5th-straight-month-at-0-52-in-august-123091401051_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fwpi-remains-in-deflation-for-5th-straight-month-at-0-52-in-august-123091401051_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fwpi-remains-in-deflation-for-5th-straight-month-at-0-52-in-august-123091401051_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Varanasi%20Court%20Directs%20ASI%20to%20Submit%20Objects%20Found%20During%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Survey%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20court%20in%20Varanasi%20has%20directed%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20to%20collect%20all%20the%20objects%20and%20materials%2C%20including%20those%20linked%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20found%20during%20its%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20premises%20and%20submit%20them%20to%20the%20district%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ASI%20is%20conducting%20a%20scientific%20survey%20of%20the%2017th-century%20mosque%20to%20determine%20if%20it%20was%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20temple%20structure.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20latest%20direction%20came%20in%20response%20to%20applications%20filed%20by%20petitioners%20from%20the%20temple%20side%2C%20pleading%20for%20the%20securing%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20Masjid%20premises%20and%20regulation%20or%20restriction%20of%20the%20number%20of%20Muslims%20offering%20namaz%20in%20the%20mosque%20to%20ensure%20that%20Hindu%20symbols%20and%20signs%20are%20not%20damaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHearing%20three%20applications%20filed%20by%20petitioner%20Rakhi%20Singh%2C%20district%20judge%20A.K.%20Vishvesha%2C%20on%20September%2013%2C%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20gather%20all%20the%20objects%20and%20materials%20obtained%20from%20the%20survey%20site.%20The%20court%20said%20it%20was%20appropriate%20that%20all%20objects%20related%20to%20the%20case%2C%20or%20those%20related%20to%20the%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20system%20of%20worship%2C%20or%20considered%20significant%20for%20the%20disposal%20of%20the%20case%20from%20a%20historical%20or%20archaeological%20perspective%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20or%20an%20officer%20appointed%20by%20the%20District%20Magistrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Vishvesha%20said%20that%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20would%20keep%20the%20items%20%E2%80%9Csafe%E2%80%9D%20and%20present%20them%20in%20court%20whenever%20summoned.%20The%20district%20judge%20also%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20compile%20a%20list%20of%20objects%20found%20during%20the%20survey%20and%20submit%20a%20copy%20to%20the%20court%20and%20another%20to%20the%20District%20Magistrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%20from%20the%20temple%20side%20filed%20these%20applications%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20suit%20they%20had%20initiated%20last%20year%2C%20seeking%20year-round%20access%20for%20worship%20in%20the%20Gyanvapi%20compound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20applications%20filed%20by%20the%20petitioners%20from%20the%20temple%20side%20alleged%20that%20the%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%2C%20the%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masajid%2C%20Varanasi%2C%20intended%20to%20damage%20signs%20and%20symbols%20of%20the%20Hindu%20faith%20inside%20the%20mosque.%20Petitioner%20Rakhi%20Singh%20said%20that%20the%20security%20of%20the%20entire%20Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20premises%20be%20secured%20to%20protect%20%E2%80%9Cevidence%E2%80%9D%20that%20had%20emerged%20from%20the%20local%20court%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20survey%20last%20year.%20However%2C%20the%20commissioner%E2%80%99s%20report%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20admitted%20by%20the%20court%2C%20nor%20have%20its%20findings%20been%20discussed%20before%20they%20are%20considered%20as%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masajid%20refuted%20all%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20the%20petitioner%20from%20the%20temple%20side%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20submissions%20in%20the%20three%20applications%20are%20%E2%80%9Cfalse.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20Masjid%20argued%20that%20the%20petitioner%20from%20the%20temple%20side%20had%20filed%20the%20applications%20%E2%80%9Cout%20of%20malice%E2%80%9D%20to%20prevent%20Muslims%20from%20offering%20namaz%20in%20the%20mosque.%20The%20caretakers%20of%20the%20mosque%20also%20submitted%20in%20the%20district%20court%20that%20all%20the%20items%20found%20during%20the%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20were%20untouched%20and%20intact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllahabad%20high%20court%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20Pritinker%20Diwaker%2C%20had%20on%20August%203%20dismissed%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%20challenging%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20judge%E2%80%99s%20July%2021%20order%20for%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20premises%20by%20the%20ASI.%20While%20restoring%20the%20order%20passed%20by%20the%20district%20judge%2C%20Varanasi%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20Diwaker%20had%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20scientific%20survey%2Finvestigation%20proposed%20to%20be%20carried%20out%E2%80%9D%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnecessary%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20justice%20and%20shall%20benefit%20the%20plaintiffs%20and%20defendants%20alike%20and%20come%20in%20aid%20of%20the%20trial%20court%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20just%20decision.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20restored%20the%20order%20of%20the%20district%20judge%2C%20who%20had%20in%20July%20directed%20the%20ASI%20director%20to%20undertake%20scientific%20investigation%2C%20survey%20or%20excavation%20at%20the%20site%2C%20i.e.%2C%20settlement%20plot%20no.%209130%2C%20excluding%20the%20areas%20(the%20ablution%20tank)%20sealed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20last%20year.%20The%20district%20court%20had%20also%20directed%20the%20ASI%20to%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20scientific%20investigation%20by%20using%20GPR%20Survey%2C%20excavation%2C%20dating%20method%20and%20other%20modern%20techniques%20of%20the%20present%20structure%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20it%20had%20been%20constructed%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20structure%20of%20a%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ASI%E2%80%99s%20additional%20director%20general%2C%20Alok%20Tripathi%2C%20had%20also%20submitted%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20court%20saying%20that%20the%20ASI%20will%20conduct%20survey%2C%20documentation%2C%20photography%2C%20detail%20description%2C%20GPR%20survey%20and%20full%20studies%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20harming%20the%20existing%20structures%E2%80%9D.%20The%20ASI%20would%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20survey%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law%20and%20prepare%20a%20list%20of%20the%20antiquities%20which%20are%20found%20in%20the%20building%20and%20carry%20out%20a%20detailed%20survey%20and%20undertake%20the%20exercise%20to%20find%20the%20age%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20structure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETripathi%20informed%20the%20court%20that%20the%20survey%20works%20would%20be%20carried%20out%20without%20any%20damage%20to%20the%20structures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientific%20investigation%20would%20be%20carried%20out%20beyond%20the%20structure%20and%20in%20open%20areas%20only%3B%20no%20drilling%2C%20no%20cutting%2C%20no%20removal%20of%20brick%20or%20stones%20from%20the%20existing%20structure%20will%20be%20done%20while%20conducting%20the%20survey%20and%20study.%20The%20entire%20survey%20would%20be%20conducted%20by%20non-destructive%20method%20by%20using%20techniques%20such%20as%20GPR%20survey%2C%20GPS%20survey%2C%20other%20scientific%20methods%20and%20other%20modern%20techniques.%20In%20case%20any%20further%20investigation%20or%20excavation%20was%20required%2C%20the%20ASI%20would%20seek%20permission%20of%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694707408000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F07141300%2FKashi-gyanvapi_1-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvaranasi-court-directs-asi-to-submit-objects-found-during-gyanvapi-mosque-survey%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20court%20asked%20the%20survey%20team%20to%20hand%20over%20all%20relevant%20objects%2C%20including%20those%20tied%20to%20the%20case%2C%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20worship%20system%2C%20to%20the%20District%20Magistrate%20or%20a%20designated%20officer.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvaranasi-court-directs-asi-to-submit-objects-found-during-gyanvapi-mosque-survey%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22RBI%20releases%20list%20of%2015%20NBFCs%20in%20upper%20layer%20under%20scale%20based%20regulations%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694706612000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-01%2F29%2Ffull%2F1674994705-7518.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frbi-names-15-nbfcs-in-upper-layer-under-scale-based-regulation-for-fy24-123091401292_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22All%20deposit-taking%20NBFCs%20and%20non-deposit-taking%20NBFCs%20with%20an%20asset%20size%20over%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20are%20in%20the%20middle%20layer%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompa